milestones.description: Stackpole has become the top scorer for AUS in ODIs with 163 runs, going past Ian Chappell's 144
Stackpole's 61 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AUS), surpassing Ian Chappell's 60
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for ENG, going past D'Oliveira
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
Geoff Arnold has become the top wicket-taker for ENG in ODIs with 6 wickets, going past Bob Woolmer's 4
Barry Wood has broken the record for most catches (2) in ODIs for ENG, going past Ken Shuttleworth's 1
Mallett has broken the record for most catches (2) in ODIs for AUS, going past Bill Lawry's 1
Barry Wood has broken the record for most catches in an innings (2) in ODIs for ENG, going past Ken Shuttleworth's 1
Rod Marsh has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (4) in ODIs for AUS, going past Rod Marsh's 1
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 76-run partnership is the highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 48 between Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss
Fletcher and Barry Wood's 39-run partnership is the highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between D'Oliveira and Hampshire
Dennis Lillee and Jeff Hammond's 22-run partnership is the highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 12 between Alan Knott and Ken Shuttleworth
Bob Massie and Jeff Hammond's 21-run partnership is the highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 18 between John Snow and Geoff Arnold
Rod Marsh has broken the record for most dismissals (7) in ODIs, going past Alan Knott's 6
This is the lowest match aggregate (359) involving teams England & Australia in ODIs
Rod Marsh has broken the record for most dismissals in an innings (4) in ODIs, going past Alan Knott's 3
Dennis Amiss has become the top scorer in ODIs with 168 runs, going past Ian Chappell's 144
Geoff Arnold has become the highest wicket-taker in ODIs with 6 wickets, going past Mallett's 5
Mallett has broken the record for most catches (2) in ODIs, going past Bill Lawry's 1
Geoff Boycott has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4), going past Greg Chappell
Barry Wood has broken the record for most catches in an innings (2) in ODIs, going past Greg Chappell's 1
Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss's 76-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 48 between Geoff Boycott and Dennis Amiss
Fletcher and Barry Wood's 39-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between D'Oliveira and Hampshire
Tony Greig and Barry Wood's 11-run partnership is ENG's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between Ray Illingworth and John Edrich
Doug Walters and Stackpole's 24-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between Paul Sheahan and Ross Edwards
